{
  "text": "Cholesterol treatment is beneficial for neurological development and neuropsychological symptom treatment, and is widely used in Europe. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] However, the reports of cholesterol treatment for SLOS in Japan are limited. We report a Japanese SLOS case with a novel mutation in DHCR7 who was diagnosed early in life with 46,XY DSD and Y-shaped 2-3 toe syndactyly, and was treated with cholesterol.",
